cs.CL, cs.CV, cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.DL

Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on developing a system for transcription of historical documents using machine learning techniques. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is also likely as the paper proposes an approach based on character segmentation using a convolutional neural network. 
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is relevant as the paper aims to support knowledge discovery from historical documents conserved in the Vatican Secret Archives. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is relevant as the paper uses machine learning techniques for character recognition and language modeling. 
- cs.DL (Deep Learning) is also relevant as the paper uses a convolutional neural network for character recognition.
